{
  "texts": [
    "We now investigate robustness under varying syntax: we fix the data structure to edge-list and re-encode the Erdős test graphs by each of the following encodings: json, NetworkX, and PyG.",
    "json is a common text-based serialization for storage and data exchange; NetworkX and PyG follow code-based conventions from graph processing libraries (cf. fig.",
    "8a in Appendix).",
    "We choose these as widely represented in pretraining corpora, potentially better activating the models' reasoning abilities.We evaluate G1, Qwen and gpt-oss on the newly encoded graphs and study the performance impact of these formats, also compared to the \"standard\" Erdős encoding.",
    "Results are all reported aggregated in fig. 4 and in full in fig."
  ]
}